<blockquote>
<p>Do I need to import some sort of timer library or will the timer class work without it?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>You need to import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Timer. The Timer the code snippet is referencing is from wpilib, and not java.util.Timer.</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="arael" data-post="8" data-topic="402381">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/b5a626/48.png" class="avatar"> arael:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>What does the exclamation mark inside the if statement parameters do?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>It means “NOT”. It inverts the value logically. So if you have if(!true) { doSomething()}, it means if it is not true, doSomething(). In code example above it means if 5 seconds has NOT elapsed, set the drivetrain to .5.</p>
