</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Anything you want to do should have their initialization done in <em>autonomousInit()</em> and <em>autonomousPeriodic()</em>.</p>
<p>If you wanted to drive for 5 seconds, but at 2 seconds turn on the shooter:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">Timer m_timer = new Timer();
....
public void autonomousInit(){
    timer.start();
}

public void autonomousPeriodic(){
    if( m_timer.hasElapsed(2){
        m_shooter.shoot();
    }

    if(! m_timer.hasElapsed(5) ){  // False if below the number
        m_drivetrain.drive(.5); // Whatever code it takes to drive your robot
    }
}
.....
</code></pre>
